m epigraphic and literary sources to visual and material artifacts. As a result, Death, Power, and Apotheosis in Ancient Egypt is an important contribution to current scholarship in its collection and presentation of data, the framework it establishes for identifying distinguished and deified dead, and its novel argumentation, which adds to the larger academic conversation about power negotiation and the perceived agency of the dead in ancient Egypt.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aApotheosiszEgyptxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aDeathzEgyptxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aPower (Social sciences)zEgyptxHistoryyTo 1500. 4aAncient History & Classical Studies. 4aArchaeology. 4aReligious Studies. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Egypt.2bisacsh  apower in the pyramid age, Apotheosis in ancient Egypt, Deified Dead in ancient Egypt, Egyptian mortuary culture, Why the Old Kingdom collapsed, Heqaib.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021 Englishz978311075405608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021z9783110753813oZDB-23-DGD40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150176017440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501760174423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501760174/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075405-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBK